🎯 React State (useState Hook)

This is one of the MOST IMPORTANT React concepts.

Without State:

❌ No counters

❌ No forms

❌ No shopping carts

❌ No dashboards

❌ No dynamic UI

State makes React applications interactive.

1. What is State?

State is data that can change while the application is running.

React watches this data.

When state changes:

React automatically updates the UI.


Example

Imagine a counter:

Count: 0

User clicks:

Count: 1

User clicks again:

Count: 2

The changing value is State.


2. Why Do We Need State?

Suppose:

let count = 0;

Button click:

count++;

React won't update the screen.

Why?

Because React does not track normal variables.


tate solves this.

const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

React now tracks changes.

When updated:

setCount(1);

React re-renders automatically.


3. Real World Analogy

Think of a digital scoreboard.

Without State
Scoreboard
----------
0

Player scores.

Internal score changes.

Screen stays:

0

😢

With State
Scoreboard
----------
