8. Real-World Example
E-Commerce Cart
import { useState } from "react";

function Cart() {
  const [items, setItems] = useState(0);

  return (
    <>
      <h2>Cart Items: {items}</h2>

      <button
        onClick={() => setItems(items + 1)}
      >
        Add Product
      </button>
    </>
  );
}

Flow:

User clicks Add Product
       ↓
items becomes 1
       ↓
UI updates
       ↓
Cart Items: 1

